content: Very good and challenging, and perfect if you need a good 30-minute distraction. Cycling runs to find good card builds is decently intuitive, but honestly im only giving this game 4 stars. The reason for that is the games difficulty. I swear, i rarely ever get past the second or third boss when my build is absolutely broken and theres 100% efficiency with my cards and how they work together. Ive only ever gotten to the last boss once with an amazing deck, but he wiped the floor with me. 4/5
Grat game would reccomend to everyone i know

Would give 0 stars if I could. Game just suffers too much RNG with cards, RNG drawing cards, and deck bloat is a GG usually. Buying packs is useless; it's not permanent and only good for that run. Extra characters too expensive. Final boss is hilariously OP and needs a mega nerf. Seriously swordmaster boss can casually slam 100+ dmg a turn and he gets 700+ hp. Snakes need a nerf on their energy gimmick. Ressurection ticket effects need a buff. Game just suffers a lot of simple gameplay problems.

Just RNG deck building. Pretty good but the game scales super fast. You need to find combos quick in order to progress far. Ended up woth my favoriye being a dual minds draw/heal appocolypse deck, i could outheal most damage, keep the cards rolling, and dish out high damage.

The game is very good. The skill of heros are totally different, hence different strategies are needed. It maybe difficult (or say hopeless) at the behinning as some of the powerful cards are locked. The difficulty is about right after unlocking those cards. I completed the story mode of all heros. The key is to limit the cards nos and maximise the heroes' skill. The only drawback is that the storyline is a bit too weak and similar. I can figure out who is the final boss at the beginning.
I felt the game was difficult to progress pass the third boss. It is grindy for other characters (not much reward once you die) and does not seem to scale properly with the player's character.

content: I no longer like this game. Since the latest "Abyss" update, the previous Season Pass which will unlock the Assassin character at Level 50 was gone, and replaced with another pass which we need to BUY AGAIN. Also, the reason why I quit this game is because I wanted to save my profile to the cloud using the "Save Profile" function, but then I accidentally clicked "Restore Profile", and WITHOUT a confirmation, my profile was rolled back to a point where I would have to play for more than 30 continuous hours just to be back where I was. Also, the "Abyss" mode is too difficult because of the "Sanity" feature, where having less than 60% Sanity gives the "Madness" debuff feature, which although says that the Madness card has the 30% chance to be drawn, it usually filled my entire deck of 5 cards (stastically 0.243% chance to occur). Only players who purchase a lot of virtual currency in this game using real cash would enjoy this game by breaking those paywalls.

content: i love it really well made game

Nice Card rougelike games with balanced yet challenging gameplay.Each characters have their own passive which given more ways to go into the games thus the adventure was random al the time that's make it the best card rougelike game.✨

You build your deck as you go and make a lot of balance decisions when thinning your deck to see if you have enough energy, dps, and defense to ultimately defeat the 4th boss of each character class. Game gets pretty easy once you do a bunch of runs to unlock better cards. You can actually use every character but the ones you don't buy can be used once per day as long as you watch an ad. Every character has a gimmick trait that you should be optimizing your deck for. Otherwise, you will lose.
In My Opinion, Its Very Addicting and Challenging makes you want to play again when you lose. People who said its to hard, they just dont know how to play this type of game.

this game is a lot of fun. the cards arent all balanced - they have differing power levels by design. the people saying its geared toward pay to win are wrong. ive won multiple times with every class and havent bought any cards. that said, the game is absolutely worth some money - its provided me hours of entertainment already, and will provide more. the game is a challenge, but when you overcome it with a strong deck its very satisfying.
